numeric_data = df.select_dtypes(include=['float64', 'int64']).columns
df[numeric_data] = df[numeric_data].fillna(df[numeric_data].median())

#filling the categorical data with mode
categorical_data = df.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns
df[categorical_data] = df[categorical_data].apply(lambda x: x.fillna(x.mode()[0]))

In[]:
def remove_outliers_iqr(df, column):
    Q1 = df[column].quantile(0.25)
    Q3 = df[column].quantile(0.75)
    IQR = Q3 - Q1
    lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
    upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR
    return df[(df[column] >= lower_bound) & (df[column] <= upper_bound)]

# Remove outliers for Tenure
df = remove_outliers_iqr(df, 'Tenure')

# Remove outliers for WarehouseToHome
df = remove_outliers_iqr(df, 'WarehouseToHome')

# Check the shape of the data after removing outliers
print('Shape of data after removing outliers:', df.shape)

Shape of data after removing outliers: (5624, 20)

Hour Spent on App: Customers who spend more time on the app tend to order more (0.58).

Negative correlation:
Days Since Last Order: Customers who order more frequently have fewer days between orders (-0.42).
Other:
Weaker correlations exist for other features, requiring further investigation.
Customer ID has no significant correlation with churn.

MODEL SELECTION

In[]:
# Encode categorical variables
categorical_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=['object', 'category']).columns
for col in categorical_cols:
    le = LabelEncoder()
    df[col] = le.fit_transform(df[col].astype(str))

# Split the data into features and target variable
X = df.drop(columns=['Churn'])
y = df['Churn']

# Scale the features
scaler = StandardScaler()
X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)

# Split the data into training and testing sets
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X_scaled, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)
In[]:
# Initialize the models
log_reg = LogisticRegression()
rf = RandomForestClassifier()
gb = GradientBoostingClassifier()
xgb = XGBClassifier()

# Train and evaluate the models
models = {'Logistic Regression': log_reg, 
          'Random Forest': rf, 
          'Gradient Boosting': gb, 
          'XGBoost': xgb}

results = {}

for model_name, model in models.items():
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
    f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred)
    roc_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_pred)
    
    # Cross-validation score
    cv_score = cross_val_score(model, X_scaled, y, cv=5, scoring='accuracy').mean()
    
    results[model_name] = {'Accuracy': accuracy, 
                           'F1 Score': f1, 
                           'ROC AUC Score': roc_auc, 
                           'Cross-Validation Score': cv_score}

results_df = pd.DataFrame(results).T
results_df
